        {
            "id": "intro_string_operations",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "String Operations",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Strings have many useful operations that help us work with text. We can do things like finding the length of the string, changing the case, and accessing individual characters."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "string_length",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "String Length",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "We can find out how many characters are in a string using the `len()` function."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The `len()` function in Python counts the number of characters in a string and returns that number. You pass the string inside the parentheses `()`, and `len()` will tell you its length."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "length = len(\"Hello\")\nprint(length)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "5"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "string_case_operations",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Changing Case",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "We can also change the strings to uppercase or lowercase."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "To change the string to uppercase, use the `.upper()` method."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "name = \"alice smith\"\nprint(name.upper())",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "ALICE SMITH"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "string_case_operations",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "To change the string to lowercase, use the `.lower()` method."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "name = \"alice smith\"\nprint(name.lower())",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "alice smith"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "string_case_operations",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "One more thing, we can also remove the whitespace from the beginning and end of the string using the `.strip()` method."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "name = \"  alice smith  \"\nprint(name.strip())",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "alice smith"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
